<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101007338966053></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101007338966053><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=101007338966053>RE: Camp at 29?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=101007338966053#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=133091><span id= >USAFknight</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>6 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jan 3rd 10:56 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm trying to remember the details, but I remember taking the boat to FV, getting off at the first stop, some kind of elven outpost in a ocean zone, sorry don't remember the name, haven't played in a long time. Now go through the elven outpost and walk out the gate, levitate and head out over the ocean after making a sharp right. You need to keep your eye open for a glacier. On this glacier are some type of yeti's that will be spaced out fairly far apart and range from a blue con to a red con for a 29 druid. Exp is excellent and very few people went to the trouble of going out there. I'll update if I remember any names or places.<br>&nbsp;<br>Kylun, 14th circle initiate of Tunare<br></td></tr>
