<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100869249529577></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100869249529577><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=100869249529577>RE: trade skills</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=100869249529577#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=63996><span id=Scholar>chking</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>41 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Dec 18th 11:21 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.06]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Trade skills have three purposes, IMHO:<br><br>1) Alleviating boredom: Working on trade skills and producing things is fun, and a good diversion from kill, loot, level.<br><br>2) Socials: Trade skills bring players together. When a player needs a certain pot or piece of armor, they can either learn to make it (see above), buy it (not always an option), or find someone who can make it. They usually opt for the third, and that gets folks talking.<br><br>3) Money! There are some things that you want, need, or just think might be neat. You can either buy it or make it. For the poor, you learn a trade skill. If you're a druid , learn Tailoring to make your own armor. If you want to make some good money, learn Blacksmithing and sell banded. Or, become a Brewer and get everyone trashed for a fee.<br><br>All in all, trade skills are fun, diverting, and profitable. Good luck!<br><br>Lambeau, Lord of Lavastorm*<br>Druid of Tunare in his 14th season<br>Saryrn server<br><br>*: Self-proclaimed<br>&nbsp;<br>-- <br>Lord Lambeau Farstrider<br>Human Druid of Tunare<br>Lords and Ladies<br>Saryrn<br>"Port: Don't leave home without it."<br><br></td></tr>
