	   <tr><td colspan=2>I started with a Dwarven Paladin and have worked him through 31.&nbsp;&nbsp;Here's my 2cp and it's only mine so feel free to have your own opinions.<br><br>Paladins are highly underutilized in groups because groups would rather have a pure tank and your spells are to weak to be effective through the teens until 30, then at 30 I found Heal to be less effective on my group.<br><br>More on tanking, you hit as well as any tank though you still don't seem to hit as hard as warriors.  Bash is decent for it's stun effect, but it doesn't always interupt for some reason so it's spotty at best.  <br><br>In six months plus I have never been highly prized in groups and Paladins solo poorly.  I found myself having to lay hands at times fighting blues.<br><br>The only true place we are prized is in undead dungeons, so I spent my time in Kurns, Befallen and Unrest most recently.  It was after getting bored with bashing skeletons that prompted me to make a Necro, which I love and have only recently gotten slightly bored (at 36) and thus started my Druid, who is 11th as I write this.<br><br>Hope that helps, I do not recommend paladins despite them fitting my nature to the T.<br>&nbsp;<br>Balnort Kindheart<br>Paladin<br><br>Balnore<br>Shaman and Master Blacksmith<br><br>Fabriss Boneshadow<br>Necromanc</td></tr>
