<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100825995853701></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100825995853701><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=100825995853701>RE: Druid soloing</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=100825995853701#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=109539><span id=Scholar>regnon</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>26 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Dec 13th 11:12 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Some advice that i have found is that when you solo as a druid, your object is to NOT get hit at all, so I feel you really dont need your buffs up at all. Only buffs i keep going are Sow, and maybe a dmg coat, and regen. I know you dont have these yet. But for later in the game they are pretty good. first off, go sit in kelethin and get all your spell skills MAXXED, this helps lots. Second, as a druid you should be trying to not get hit at all like i stated before. Third, DOT work much better when the mob is not standing still regening its self. So run those little orcs a ways. Then root them. Makes things much easier.<br>SO anyway short list of spells you might want to mem , Heal, Sow, DMG coat, S Swarm, G Roots, Snare and a DD you like (personaly the lighting spells are my favorite till you get to COMBUST) These spells should make it way easier to solo. Basicly you have to decide WHEN to use the spells thats when the problms might arise. I would say Snare, Dot, run little bit, Root , dot again , med, dd , creature should be dead. MY 2cp<br>&nbsp;<br>What the heck was that?.....darn Pixie stinger!!!<br></td></tr>
