	   <tr><td colspan=2>You sure about that info on DOT?&nbsp;&nbsp;I thought if the mob was moving, it will only do 66% of the damage...?  My usual method is to pull with snare, back up and DD.  If snare does not stick, root attempt to snare again then throw a DoT on and med till root breaks and continue with kiting.  The fizzles with the DOT spells are normal at lower levels.  If you have practices to spare, throw a few into conjuration (I think its conjuration hehe).  Just keep using it when you can, more for the skill raises than for actual damage<br><br>Yulius Bearenemy<br>20 Druid<br>&nbsp;<br>Quanko Crakkers<br>57 Monk<br>Xegony</td></tr>
